  "prompt": "I work in a hotel. My manager keeps the fire alarm off. Is it legal?",
  "response": "It's generally illegal and highly unsafe for a hotel or any public facility to keep fire alarms off. Fire alarm systems are crucial for the safety of guests and staff, alerting everyone in the event of a fire or other emergencies. Building codes and fire safety regulations typically require functional fire alarm systems to be in place in hotels and similar establishments.\n\nIf your manager is intentionally disabling the fire alarm system, this not only poses a significant safety risk but may also violate local, state, or federal regulations. It's important to report these concerns to local authorities, such as the fire marshal or building inspection department, to ensure the safety of everyone in the hotel. If you feel comfortable, you may also consider discussing this situation with a higher authority within the company or an employee rights organization.",
